explanation: This solution uses a stack to keep track of the opening brackets and a map to map closing brackets to their corresponding opening brackets. It iterates through the string, pushing opening brackets onto the stack and popping them off when a corresponding closing bracket is encountered. If the stack is empty at the end or if a closing bracket does not match the top of the stack, the string is invalid. This approach has a high efficiency due to the constant time operations of the stack and map lookups.

